## Limitations
The findings are based on available literature and expert opinions, which may not cover all aspects of loneliness and its impact on mental health. The subjective nature of loneliness means that its effects can vary widely among individuals. Additionally, the data is primarily from Western contexts, which may not fully represent global experiences of loneliness. Further research is needed to explore cultural differences and the long-term effects of loneliness on mental health.